-lrb- cnn -rrb- thursday will mark three weeks since saudi arabia began airstrikes on houthi rebels in yemen . but there is as yet little sign that the rebels are being driven back , that the fighting in yemen is dying down or that lives there are being saved .
since it began on march 26 , saudi arabia has launched more than 1,200 airstrikes . saudi officials claim to have killed more than 500 houthi rebels .